column3: Tested ACK 4818dba90074f213efa0fa7faf577ce5fb02eaee (I get roughly the same seeds)\n

I'm still not on the list. :( I have been running a node consistently at 68.34.102.231 for quite a while. I did a little investigation back in https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/6333 and found that it was probably something to do with IPv6, so I have been running onlynet=ipv4. http://bitcoin.sipa.be/seeds.txt shows my node at almost 100% up-time.\n
Prefer to avoid listing nodes that have a specific interest in being on the list anyway.\n

My motivation is to make sure that the list of hardcoded seeds is accurate. For the 1 data point that I have direct knowledge of (my own node), it does not appear that the list is accurate. If I was interested in attacking the bitcoin network, there would be much more effective ways that getting my node on this list.\n\nEither way, I manually verified about a dozen of the nodes on the new list and
If somebody wants to compare the output, my dns seeders data would be here:\nhttps://bitcoin.jonasschnelli.ch/dnsseed.dump\n

@PRabahy I have no idea why you're not listed, but if it appears in seeds.txt it should be straightforward to trace it through the `makeseeds.py` script and see which filter pass "eats" it.\n(and maybe correct the script if you think it does so for no good reason)\n
@PRabahy your weekly uptime is 87% (sipa) or 86% ([21](https://bitnodes.21.co/nodes/leaderboard/?q=68.34.102.231#leaderboard)). I don't think this is enough to get into the list.\n
